{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd56a632-98f7-47c4-83ea-a8ec2899fdea","content":"I can help point you in the right direction. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them — so it won't apply here.\n\nFor **analyzing** a `.dmp` file, use one of these tools:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — .NET CLI tool for managed analysis\n   - Install: `dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump`\n   - Commands: `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, `gcroot`\n\n2. **`lldb` with SOS plugin** — on Linux/macOS\n\n3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio** — on Windows\n\n**Quick triage steps with `dotnet-dump analyze`:**\n```bash\n# Launch analysis\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n\n# Inside the REPL:\n> pe              # Print last exception (usually the crash cause)\n> clrstack -all   # Show managed call stacks for all threads\n> dumpheap -stat  # Check for memory issues\n```\n\nThe `pe` (print exception) command is typically the fastest way to find the root cause — it shows the exception type, message, and stack trace that caused the crash.\n\nWould you like help installing `dotnet-dump` or running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"292243c2-fd63-4b7d-8192-f58267c367e6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":439,"requestId":"5FC9:1F4026:DE1736:102294B:69EACBF9"},"id":"96b7851a-d382-4506-8362-715afcadfd16","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:48:52.659Z","parentId":"dc593a